events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson watched his second 3-pointer go down, turned toward the Pelicans' defensive end and threw a triumphant punch into the air.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores 35 again, Pelicans top Suns 129-124 in OT

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 35 points, Anthony Davis had 34 points and 15 rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Detroit Pistons 124-117 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James, Davis carry Lakers past Pistons, 124-117

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle and RJ Barrett each scored 27 points and the New York Knicks ran their winning streak to a season-high four games, beating the Sacramento Kings 112-99 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks beat Kings 112-99 for 4th straight victory

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 23 points, Paolo Banchero added 20 points and 12 rebounds and the Orlando Magic beat the Toronto Raptors 111-99 Sunday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner, Banchero lead Magic past Raptors for 3rd win in row

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 53 points and 11 rebounds, leading the Philadelphia 76ers to a 131-113 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 53, leads 76ers to 131-113 win over Hornets

headlines.description: — A.J. Griffin hit a 6-footer on an alley-oop pass at the overtime buzzer and the Atlanta Hawks snapped a three-game losing streak with a 123-122 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Sunday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin wins game at OT buzzer, Hawks hold off Bulls 123-122

headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 30 points and seven rebounds, Kevin Porter Jr. added 18 points and seven assists and the Houston Rockets beat the Milwaukee Bucks 97-92 on Sunday night to extend their home-winning streak to four games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 30 points, Rockets beat Bucks 97-92
